fine its central concepts. They show how these concepts can improve conventional models as well as generate new ideas, hypotheses, and empirical approaches, and conclude by outlining an agenda of theoretical development and empirical research to create and test complex systems theories of issue-areas of world politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aComplexity (Philosophy). 0aInternational relationsxMethodology. 0aInternational relationsxPhilosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aAxelrod, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBhavnani, Ravi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aClemens, Walter C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEarnest, David C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrison, Neil E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarrison, Neil E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoffmann, Matthew J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenau, James N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSandole, Dennis J. D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaunders-Newton, Desmond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSinger, J. David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791481493423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791481493/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-all